<TEXT>
a gunman robbed a bank tuesday kidnapped 
the bank manager and drove off in the managers car only to be 
cornered by a police roadblock on an interstate authorities said 
the manager al jacobson 61 was freed about seven hours after 
police closed interstate 176 a spur from interstate 76 leading to 
reading said terrell weaver a police communications operator 
negotiations with the gunmman continued late tuesday mrs 
weaver said 
a state police swat team and an fbi tactical team arrived at the 
scene six hours after the standoff began about 10 miles south of 
this southeast pennsylvania city said a berks county dispatch 
supervisor who declined to give her name 
a nearby access road was closed because traffic seemed to 
startle the gunman the supervisor said 
the suspects brother was brought to the scene in an effort to 
persuade him to surrender but the robber asked his brother to 
leave said the supervisor 
police asked the suspect to exchange the bank manager for an 
officer but he turned the offer down authorities said 
the man was armed with a 9mm pistol said amity township police 
chief maurice eschbach who questioned several witnesses to the 
robbery 
the robber identified by police only as a 29yearold from the 
pottstown area took the manager hostage at 4 pm at the meridian 
bank in amity township according to an fbi agent who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
police believe less than 5000 was taken said the berks county 
supervisor 
</TEXT>
