<TEXT>
is the amendment in purgatory only the 
category will tell 
the senate struggling to deal with hundreds of amendments to a 
bill providing new ammunition for the war on drugs hammered 
together a system designed to speed its work and permit congress to 
adjourn for the year 
at times it appeared that the laborandtimesaving device might 
prove a tottering house of cards that would bring all progress to a 
halt 
it worked this way 
the amendments were assigned to categories 
with some the skids were greased 
with others the road ahead was rocky indeed 
still others faced a fate uncertain 
category 1 amendments were offered as a package containing 
scores of legislative initiatives and eventually all were approved 
on a single bloc vote 
category 2 amendments might stand a chance but only if they 
were approved by a panel of senators from both parties decisions 
could be appealed to the senates republican and democratic leaders 
those are the purgatory amendments said senate republican 
leader bob dole of kansas they do not know where they are going 
and they may not be going anywhere 
category 3 amendments could be offered individually and face 
their chances 
category 4 amendments did not make the cut and had no chance at 
all 
it took unanimous consent of all 100 senators for the gears to 
mesh and the system to move forward 
the spur to getting that consent was the desire of many senators 
facing reelection contests to leave the capital and get on with 
campaigning 
sen ted stevens ralaska had a complaint 
i had an amendment and i find it is not even on the purgatory 
list he said 
that raises the question to me whether my amendment went to 
heaven or hell he said 
how do i find that out 
it went to hell replied sen phil gramm rtexas 
stevens i know the senator from texas might want me to go 
there but where did my amendment go 
dole it is on list no 4 
what happens to list no 4 stevens asked 
nothing dole replied 
