millions of dollars into state coffers including muchneeded money 
for education and rural economic development 
twentyeight states and the district of columbia operate 
lotteries which have grossed 148 billion in fiscal 1988 up 192 
percent from 1987 according to gambling and wagering business 
magazine based in new york of that sum 56 billion went to state 
governments and the balance to cover prizes and the cost of 
administration according to lottery officials 
