said 
the royal swedish academy of sciences which awards the prize 
said allais was chosen for his pioneering contributions to the 
theory of markets and efficient utilization of resources 
although littleknown outside france allais was extremely 
influential at home where senior officials in key government 
ministries and stateowned industries have enormous economic power 
jacques levy director of the ecole nationale des mines from 
which allais officially retired nine years ago while continuing 
his research and writing said the new laureate had a decisive 
effect on economic thinking for more than two decades 
he was the mentor for everyone involved in the economy in 
postwar france between 1945 and 1968 all the people who were in 
charge of the biggest enterprises and of the state planning 
apparatus levy said 
within the world of french economic thought after world war ii 
in which leftists and rightists agreed the state should play a 
major role in the economy allais established a place for reliance 
on market forces 
he worked on a system of definition of prices which would 
permit the economy to function at its best levy said 
allaiss work provided a very strong base for those opposed to 
government direction of the economy said jacques lautman 
scientific director for human sciences at frances national center 
for scientific research 
allais said he hoped the nobel prize would allow him to continue 
his work even though he is past the official retirement age 
im happy to have the nobel prize to show how absurd this 
situation is he said its amazing that politicians think its 
normal that they should not retire while they think its normal to 
push scholars into retirement 
