<DOCNO> AP881018-0189 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
federal regulators announced approval tuesday 
of an experimental plan for coordinated trading halts or circuit 
breakers in stock and futures markets during steep price dives 
the plan proposed by the new york stock exchange and the 
chicago mercantile exchange provides for a onehour trading halt 
across markets when the dow jones average of 30 industrial stocks 
plunges by 250 points or more from the previous days closing 
it calls for a twohour halt when the dow falls by 400 points 
the securities and exchange commission which regulates the 
stock markets and the commodity futures trading commission which 
oversees futures exchanges approved the oneyear experiment on the 
eve of the first anniversary of the oct 19 1987 stock crash 
the new york stock exchange is the nations largest stock market 
and the chicago mercantile exchange is the largest market for 
trading stock index futures 
other markets including the chicago board options exchange the 
american stock exchange and the national association of securities 
dealers overthecounter system are joining in the plan 
government approval is effective immediately it is up to the 
exchanges to decide when the circuit breaker plan begins 
were ready to implement this as soon as thursday said 
andrew yemma a spokesman for the chicago mercantile exchange we 
think this is a very significant action to remedy what problems 
there were in the market a year ago 
the new york stock exchange did not give a specific start time 
but said it would be very soon 
the plan is designed to provide an orderly halt to trading 
before one market stock or futures breaks down shifting all of 
the trading to the remaining market it also is intended to allow 
time for buyers to step in and counter overwhelming sell orders 
during the 1987 crash the dow plunged a record 508 points 
wiping out 500 billion in paper wealth in a single day 
another part of the program gives individual investors as 
opposed to pension and mutual funds preference in trading on the 
new york stock exchange when the dow moves either up or down by 25 
points the rule applies to orders of 2099 shares and smaller 
after the crash many individual investors complained that their 
orders were shunted aside in some cases for hours while larger 
buy and sell orders from institutional investors were executed 
the market halt plan is one of the key recommendations offered 
after the crash by a presidential task force headed by nicholas 
brady a new york investment banker who is now treasury secretary 
brady did not offer a specific proposal but said some sort of 
circuit breaker was needed to derail a crash 
the national association of securities dealers said earlier this 
month that it was going along with the plan only reluctantly 
because it did not want to be the only market left open when all 
others were closed 
but nasd president joseph r hardiman argued that a 
preannounced trigger for market halts could act as a magnet 
pulling the market down faster as the market approaches the 
trading halt limit it could be flooded with orders from traders 
fearful they will be prevented from selling he said 
with the sec approval which is effective immediately a 
previous sixmonth experiment to curb computerized index arbitrage 
ends the earlier program had imposed a socalled 50point collar 
on the new york stock exchange when the market moved by 50 points 
or more index arbitrage orders were not allowed through the nyses 
automated trading system 
index arbitrage is a form of trading designed to take advantage 
of momentary price discrepancies between the stocks and futures 
markets it involves the buying and selling of massive orders on 
stocks and futures markets and was criticized for making last 
years crash more precipitous 
however the collar experiment ran counter to the brady 
commissions finding that stock and future markets were in effect 
one market and that disconnecting them could be dangerous 
a new rule taking the place of the collar is designed to provide 
more orderly index arbitrage when the standard and poors 500 index 
falls by more than 12 points the equivalent of 96 points on the 
dow index arbitrage orders will be shunted into a side file of 
the trading computer if buy and sell orders can be matched the 
trades will go through if not trading in individual sampp 500 
stocks could be halted 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

