<TEXT>
the mandalay ruby a royal red gem that weighs 
48 carats was supposed to sell for a record 15 million at auction 
tuesday 
it didnt 
instead a high bid of 76 million was rejected as insufficient 
by the gems owner and the ruby which sothebys earlier called 
the centerpiece of the most important jewelry sale ever held in 
america was taken off the block 
meanwhile christies auction house announced that the largest 
diamond ever auctioned to the public would be offered at a sale 
wednesday 
the 40748carat gem is second in size only to the 53020carat 
cullinan i which is set in britains imperial sceptre as part of 
the crown jewels 
im certain this jewel will set a record price for a single 
precious stone said francois curiel head of christies jewelry 
department 
he refused to estimate the price the record auction price for 
any jewel 931 million the amount paid in april 19 for an 
8591carat white diamond at sothebys 
the diamond currently owned by two new york jewelry dealers and 
a jewelry retail chain in dallas was purchased as an uncut 
890carat stone in august 1984 but has since been cut into a 
flawless stone 
at sothebys auction house tuesday about 300 people strained 
their necks to catch a glimpse of those who put up the 
multimilliondollar bids for the mandalay ruby but the 
auctioneers gavel slammed down a short time later to end the 
bidding without a sale 
jennifer brown a sothebys spokeswoman said the identity of 
the rubys seller would not be revealed 
obviously were disappointed said john d block head of 
sothebys jewelry department this was expected to bring a record 
and it didnt it was such an enormous price we were trying to get 
on unique objects its very hard to put a price on it sometimes 
it doesnt work 
the ruby was offered in the same session as the star of sierra 
leone diamond no 2 which was sold for 352 million tuesday the 
diamond is one of 11 stones cut from a 969carat diamond discovered 
in the west african nation in 1972 
several mandalay ruby bidders who asked not to be identified 
suggested that perhaps extensive presale publicity about the ruby 
had backfired on sothebys 
in its preauction report sothebys had given the mandalay a 
glowing review 
the combination of pleasant shape and proportions fine color 
transparency and luminosity make it an exceptional gemstone 
said a report released by the auction house 
block described the mandalay ruby as the largest faceted gem 
known and estimated it would command about 15 million 
the record price for a ruby is 19 million paid at a paris 
auction in july for a 104carat stone 
the mandalay ruby is framed by 18 diamonds within a 
goldandplatinum broach mounting small diamondset fleurdelys 
designs decorate the corners 
the mandalay ruby named after the burmese city near which it 
was mined was brought to england in 1875 it is questionable if 
the london market would ever have seen the gem but for the 
necessities of the burmese government wrote edwin w street a 
contemporary gem expert in burma the sale created intense 
excitement a military escort was considered necessary to escort 
the persons carrying the parcel to the vessel 
the gem was sold at sothebys in 1896 the buyer was reputed 
to be an important indian gem connoisseur acting on behalf of a 
royal indian family according to a note by gem expert benjamin 
zucker printed in the catalog for tuesdays sale 
