<TEXT>
the general assembly on tuesday voted to 
accept israels credentials by the widest margin in the six years 
since arab states have been making demands to disqualify the jewish 
state 
in an annual vote on membership in the 159member world body 
israel was accepted by a vote of 95 to 41 with seven abstentions 
and 16 nations absent that was 15 votes better than last year 
when the vote was 8039 with 10 abstentions 
for the past six years during the credentials vote an arab 
nation has urged acceptance of all countries except israel each 
year a nordic country has proposed the arab amendment be rejected 
israels acting ambassador johanan bein called the vote 
tuesday an impressive and very significant victory 
in the six years in which we have had this annual ritual we 
see from year to year a gradual improvement he said 
israel has been condemned by many un members for its harsh 
measures in putting down the 10month palestinian uprising in 
israelioccupied territories increasingly however the united 
nations and its members are calling for an international peace 
conference on the middle east involving israel and all parties to 
the dispute 
among the changes in voting this year were hungary which voted 
yes to accept israels credentials last year hungary was 
absent 
east germany which last year voted against israel this year 
was absent in a tentative signal of warming intentions 
other countries who switched from no votes or absences to 
yes votes were sierra leone suriname and zambia 
two new no votes came from jordan and afghanistan which 
last year were absent in july jordan severed its administrative 
ties with the west bank and distanced itself as a player in a 
middle east peace settlement 
the israeli mission spokesman baruch binah attributed the 
improved vote to an atmosphere of international reconciliation 
better eastwest ties greater pragmatism at the un and the 
increasing prestige of the world body 
