fuel was loaded into mexicos first nuclear 
power plant tuesday while congressmen argued about canceling the 
project amid the shouts of nuclear foes in the chamber of deputies 
mexico has entered the nuclear age the federal electricity 
commission announced tuesday afternoon after the loading had 
started 
commission spokesman roberto femat said between a third and a 
fourth of 92 tons of enriched uranium was put into the first 
reactor unit tuesday the second unit of the usdesigned laguna 
verde plant on the gulf of mexico in veracruz state is still under 
construction 
femat said loading could be completed in two or three days 
in mexico city 180 miles east of the plant about 400 people 
crowded the public gallery of the chamber of deputies and shouted 
laguna verde no during a congressional debate on the project 
most opposition parties are against the nuclear program that has 
been a favored project of ruling institutional revolutionary party 
pri administrations for the past 20 years 
the government calls the project proof of mexicos technical 
ability 
although the plant is usdesigned much of the construction has 
been done by mexican firms 
the commission said the laguna verde reactor would not begin 
commercial operation until it has operated at 100 percent 
efficiency for 100 continuous hours the government has said the 
tests could take six months 
there have been protests near the plant and in the cities of 
veracruz and xalapa the state capital since the government 
announced friday that fuel loading would begin within 1025 days 
many parents in palma sola a town only five miles from the 
plant kept their children out of school to protest the decision 
the mexico city newspaper excelsior said tuesday 
antinuclear groups have urged the government to reconsider its 
decision and vowed to continue their protests 
they claim the plant is obsolete and dangerous and question the 
need for nuclear power in oilrich mexico 
gonzalo martinez corbala a pri congressman and president of the 
chamber of deputies energy commission has accused the critics of 
distorting the facts and spreading misinformation 
he rejected the idea of a public referendum on nuclear power 
saying the public is not informed on the issue according to the 
government newspaper el nacional 
the laguna verde plant has been under construction since 1973 
