beiruts dividing green line that has served as temporary 
headquarters for the parliament since 1976 
the christians boycotted three previous parliament sessions 
called for aug 18 sept 22 and sept 23 to elect a successor to 
gemayel 
minutes before he bowed out 26 days ago gemayel a maronite 
catholic named aoun then army commander and also a maronite 
prime minister of a caretaker military cabinet 
but moslems claimed aouns appointment violated an unwritten 
national agreement dating to lebanons independence from france in 
1943 under which the president has always been a maronite the 
prime minister a sunni and the speaker of parliament a shiite 
the moslems pledged allegiance to the incumbent cabinet of sunni 
moslem prime minister salim hoss 
