in case george bush and michael dukakis want 
to talk about goats the agriculture department has some new 
material speechwriters can use no kidding it would be good for 
rebuttal too 
goats are among the most noncontroversial farm topics around 
they havent been involved in any huge usda subsidy flap and are 
not a big legislative issue on capitol hill 
moreover while city folk may have trouble identifying with 
modern feedlots that send beef to their tables or the farrowing 
pens that turn out pork chops and sausage just about everyone 
feels good about goats 
since before biblical times goats may have been the most 
useful of domesticated animal producing milk for drinking or for 
cheese gourmet meat cabrito leather and fiber for clothing 
cashmere or angora not to be confused with angora rabbit 
wool says the departments cooperative state research service 
the goat report is the latest in a series of singlesheet papers 
turned out by the agencys office for smallscale agriculture 
others include such topics as sheep mushrooms foliage plants 
herbs wildflowers and specialty vegetables 
goats are relatively clean and make fine pets and show 
animals the report said worldwide there may be as many 460 
million which produce an estimated 45 million metric tons of milk 
annually 
but before people quit the city job politics or other endeavor 
there are some things they should know about raising goats for a 
living or as a supplement to other income 
they of course need care to keep dogs away and skillful 
management to prevent diseases and internal as well as external 
parasites such as lice mites and fleas the report said goat 
milk is so respected that there have been people who began raising 
dairy goats before learning whether they could sell the milk or 
knew how to make cheese 
one problem is that in at least 21 states goat milk must be 
pasteurized or heated to a prescribed temperature to kill 
potentially harmful bacteria and pasteurization can cost a bundle 
for equipment 
where milk can be sold raw herds must be licensed and the 
nannies must be carefully tested and kept free of brucellosis and 
tuberculosis which are contagious to humans 
lest anyone sneer at someones plan to operate a goat ranch on a 
couple of acres beyond the zoning of outer surburbia goats have 
assumed something of a washington hauteur of late 
in 1987 for the first time congress and president reagan 
recognized the merits of the dairy goat proclaiming a national 
dairy goat awareness week 
president reagan it was said supported the idea 
enthusiastically and had recalled with fondness the time about 25 
years ago when each or our two doe goats had quintuplets on our 
ranch in california 
goats are raised for nondairy purposes such as for meat and 
leather or fine hair the report said farmers and ranchers who are 
already pasturing some sheep or cattle or both may be able to add 
some goats without any problems 
goats eat some plants that sheep and cattle dont seek so 
they are not mutually exclusive the report said they pasture 
well together 
the meat or cabrito sometimes called chevon has little fat 
and tastes better than venison the report said worldwide 
production is more than 12 million metric tons a year 
with a flock of 350 to 400 spanish does bob buckholz of 
dripping springs texas who raises goats for meat annually sells 
their offspring for meat at eight months of age for 30 a head 
the report said 
since the stock is tough thrifty and hardy he has lots of 
pasture and some pyrenees dogs to keep predators such as coyotes 
and wild dogs at bay buckholzs expenses are relatively small 
tom and helen hill lake butler fla sometimes feed young 
goats or kids only about two months until they reach 35 to 40 
pounds the young animals are then sold at nearly 1 a pound in the 
miami area where there is often a shortage of goats in november 
and december 
for free single copies of the report goats or any of the 
others published so far write to office for smallscale 
agriculture cooperative state research service office of grants 
and program systems room 342d aerospace building usda 
washington dc 202512200 telephone 202 4473640 
