<TEXT>
an agreement between illinois and a british 
agency to share securities information is the first of its kind 
between a us state and a foreign regulatory body a state 
association said tuesday 
illinois agreement with the british underscores the vital 
role that the states can play in policing our increasingly 
interconnected securities markets said john c baldwin 
president of the north american securities administrators 
association 
much of the securities enforcement in the us is carried out 
at the state level he said so it makes good sense that state 
securities agencies should play a crucial role in the oversight of 
global securities markets 
the accord was signed oct 12 by illinois secretary of state jim 
edgar and robert p wilkinson director of enforcement for the 
securities association in great britain the largest stock market 
selfregulatory organization operating under the united kingdoms 
financial services act 
however the pact was not announced until the national 
organization representing 50 state securities agencies received a 
firm indication that tsas board would approve it at their next 
meeting nov 7 said scott staff a spokesman for the us group 
it is similar to an agreement between tsa and the american stock 
exchange and to ones reached recently between the us securities 
and exchange commission and canadian provinces and territories the 
nasaa said 
under the accord the illinois securities department and british 
association will exchange information on securities transactions 
from their respective files for enforcement and regulatory purposes 
this agreement further establishes chicago and illinois as a 
world financial leader said edgar who oversees the activities 
of the states securities department the securities market today 
is global in character so regulation and enforcement should be 
global as well 
